## Key Improvements

1. **In-place partitioning**: Uses `swap` instead of creating new lists
2. **Tail recursion**: Uses iterative approach with manual stack management
3. **Memory efficiency**: O(1) additional space (not counting recursion stack)
4. **Type safety**: Generic over any `Ord` type
5. **Documentation**: Added comprehensive documentation and examples
6. **Testing**: Comprehensive test suite covering edge cases
7. **Safety**: Proper bounds checking and no unsafe code
8. **Performance**: Better cache locality and reduced memory allocation

The Rust version maintains the same algorithmic complexity but with significantly better performance characteristics and safety guarantees. [end of text]


